      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-problem&#34;&gt;The problem&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are &lt;code&gt;n&lt;/code&gt; cities connected by some number of flights. You are given an array &lt;code&gt;flights&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;flights[i] = [from_i, to_i, price_i]&lt;/code&gt; indicates that there is a flight from city &lt;code&gt;from_i&lt;/code&gt; to city &lt;code&gt;to_i&lt;/code&gt; with cost &lt;code&gt;price_i&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are also given three integers &lt;code&gt;src&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;dst&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;k&lt;/code&gt;, return the &lt;strong&gt;cheapest price&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;code&gt;src&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;dst&lt;/code&gt; with at most &lt;code&gt;k&lt;/code&gt; stops. If there is no such route, return &lt;code&gt;-1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
